learning_outcomes.en:
At the end of the course, students should:
1.	have a specialised knowledge and understanding of key aspects of the scientific basis of human body;
2.	describe the location of functional systems in the regions of the body. Recall facts related to: the levels of structural organisation of the human body, the gross structure and function of the major regions and systems of the body;
3.	name and describe, in standard terms, anatomical planes and relations and the gross anatomical components of the human body and explain their function;
4.	identify the major organs and musculo-skeletal elements of human specimens.

learning_outcomes.et:
1.	oskab käsitleda terviklikult inimese organismi, selle osade ehitust seoses funktsiooniga ja oskab kasutada neid teadmisi põhieriala kontekstis; 
2.	teab elundite kuju, struktuuri ja paiknemist elundsüsteemide kaupa;
3.	oskab arvestada organismi funktsionaalsete ja ealiste muutustega ning sooliste iseärasustega;
4.	orienteerub naturaalsetel preparaatidel.
